section.p: In those patients taking other medications that do not significantly inhibit or induce lamotrigine glucuronidation (see Interactions), the initial LAMICTAL dose is 25 mg once a day for two weeks, followed by 50 mg once a day for two weeks. Thereafter, the dose should be increased by a maximum of 50 to 100 mg every one to two weeks until the optimal response is achieved. The usual maintenance dose to achieve an optimal response is 100 to 200 mg/day given once a day or as two divided doses.1

In patients taking AEDs where the pharmacokinetic interaction with lamotrigine is currently not known (see Interactions), the treatment regimen as recommended for LAMICTAL with concurrent valproate should be used.

section.p: Because of a risk of rash, the initial dose and subsequent dose escalation should not be exceeded (see Warnings and Precautions).

section.p: What should you consider before taking Sample Medicine?.

p.b: Sample Medicine must not be taken if:

li.p: You are allergic to YYY, ZZZ, or any of the other ingredients listed in Section 6 of this medication.

You are taking another type of medication called an ACE inhibitor (e.g., Enalapril, Lisinopril, or Ramipril). ACE inhibitors are used to treat high blood pressure or heart failure. If you have been taking an ACE inhibitor, you should wait at least 36 hours after the last dose before starting Sample Medicine (see "Taking Sample Medicine with other medications").

You or a family member have experienced a condition called angioedema (swelling of the face, lips, tongue, and/or throat, difficulty breathing) in response to taking an ACE inhibitor or an angiotensin receptor blocker (ARB) (e.g., ZZZ, Telmisartan, or Irbesartan).

section.p: Medications that increase the amount of potassium in the blood. This includes potassium supplements, potassium-containing salt substitutes, potassium-sparing medications, and Heparin.

Tablets:
Lactose
Microcrystalline cellulose
Povidone
Sodium starch glycolate
Iron oxide yellow (E172)
Magnesium stearate
Your doctor may monitor the potassium levels in your blood regularly during treatment with Sample Medicine.
